An exciting weekend lies ahead for participants in the national finals of the 2022 World Corporate Golf Challenge (WCGC) as soft drink brand, Pepsi and the favourite brand on Guinness Nigeria stable, Singleton, have joined the prestigious class of WCGC sponsors. WCGC is the largest world corporate golf tournament in the world and Falcon Golf Development Company (Falcon Golf) is the event’s franchise holder in Nigeria. While Pepsi is offering their celebrity disc jockey, DJ Scratch and the renowned Storm Band to cool the evenings with light music, Guinness is providing Singleton single malt whiskey to make the 2022 WCGC an event to remember. Also in this elite class of WCGC sponsors are NCDMB, Henley & Partners, Banwo & Ighodalo, Geregu Power, PwC, OVH Energy, First E&P, Dradrock Real Estate, GTi Capital, Oando Resources, Rwanda Air, Multistream Power Options, J. Lindeberg, 2sure, Captain Morgan, Dubic Malt, Royal Electronics from Sims Nigeria, Lagoon Hospital and Supersport. Billed for the serene Lakowe Lakes Golf and Country Estate in Lagos from May 20 to May 22, “the national finals is a must play for discerning golfers”, says Remi Olukoya, the Chief Executive Officer of Falcon Golf, a pioneer Nigerian brand in golf course development. “It will be WCGC with a difference, a unique tournament reminiscent of the world finals itself,” Olukoya explains, adding, “This event is not an event any golfer should miss. We are going to offer value for every penny spent in this event, so, both sponsors and players are in for a great outing.” 